========================================================================
WAY 3: S-BANDS (Combined Brute-Force + CF Sieve)
========================================================================

S-band definition: prime h with ||h * 2*pi/7|| * h < 1  [mpmath dps>=200]

Sieve method:
  Phase A: brute-force prime sweep h=2..5,000,000 (all primes checked, mpmath 200 dps)
  Phase B: CF convergent denom sieve (mpmath 400 dps, 450 terms, denom to ~10^200)
           for h > 5,000,000 (brute-force impractical)
  Combined: union of Phase A and Phase B results.

alpha = 2*pi/7 = 0.89759790102565521099

PRECISION AUDIT: Meta AI float64 candidate bands (14 total)
------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Methodology: float64 arithmetic gives ~15.9 significant digits.
  For h~10^N the product h*alpha needs ~2N digits; float64 returns
  exact-integer results (norm_f64=0) for many large primes, creating
  false positives that FAIL under mpmath 200 dps.

  PHASE 1: 5 known candidates (h values from task specification)
